    "plan_content": "The plan is complete. Here's a summary of what I found and designed:\n\n---\n\n## Exploration Findings\n\nI analyzed the full IRC plugin (`extensions/irc/`) as the primary reference — it's the closest match to PulseBoard's feature set (both direct + group chat, full DM/group policy, setup wizard). I also reviewed Nostr, Telegram, and the plugin SDK contract files.\n\n## Plan: 23 New Files in `extensions/pulseboard/`\n\n**Root files** (6): `package.json`, `openclaw.plugin.json`, `index.ts`, `setup-entry.ts`, `api.ts`, `channel-config-api.ts`\n\n**Source files** (17): `types.ts`, `runtime-api.ts`, `runtime.ts`, `config-schema.ts`, `config-ui-hints.ts`, `accounts.ts`, `normalize.ts`, `client.ts`, `policy.ts`, `send.ts`, `inbound.ts`, `monitor.ts`, `probe.ts`, `setup-core.ts`, `setup-surface.ts`, `channel.ts`, `channel.test.ts`\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **No external npm deps** — PulseBoard is fictional, so `client.ts` is a stub that simulates async connection\n2. **`runtime-api.ts` without a dedicated SDK facade** — since we can't add `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` (no existing files modified), this barrel imports from general SDK subpaths, or borrows from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` (a valid public path)\n3. **Target conventions**: `#board-name` for groups, `username`/`@username` for DMs, `pulseboard:` prefix stripping\n4. **4000-char chunk limit** declared in `outbound.base.textChunkLimit` in `channel.ts`\n5. **Auth**: `PULSEBOARD_TOKEN` + `PULSEBOARD_URL` env vars, or config fields `token`/`url`\n6. **DM + group policies**: full pairing/open/allowlist/disabled support, mirroring IRC exactly",
